					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-10369980#post-4160673</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-10369980/scp-4512#post-4160673</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Thu, 21 Feb 2019 18:12:52 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>aismallard</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>4598089</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>Nice work, great seeing this finally posted! +1</p> <div class="collapsible-block"> <div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;Show&nbsp;suggestions</a></div> <div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none"> <div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">-&nbsp;Hide&nbsp;suggestions</a></div> <div class="collapsible-block-content"> <blockquote> <p>Current containment procedures include the following process:</p> </blockquote> <p>Should be &quot;processes&quot;, plural.</p> <blockquote> <p>Creation of HL-LVR aka Hukilau Lover, a world wide web crawler to find any forum posts, news articles, social media posts, etc. pertaining to the appearance of SCP-4512.</p> </blockquote> <p>I would change to &quot;HL-LVR (aka Hukilau Lover)&quot;.</p> <blockquote> <p>Name: Researcher Chevrolet</p> </blockquote> <p>Consider changing this to &quot;Involved personnel&quot;, my brain would initially misread these as being the name of the proposal rather than the name of a person.</p> <blockquote> <p>[[COMMAND INSTRUCTS RESEARCHER KALAMA TO ABORT THE INTERVIEW]]</p> </blockquote> <p>Extra [ ]s</p> <blockquote> <p>Closing Statement: Information about Hawaii is currently barred from explicitly being told to SCP-4512 until its motives are more clearly understood.</p> </blockquote> <p>To be honest I don't think this is necessary, it's already implied to not be worth the risk when Command tells the interviewer to stop talking about Hawaii.</p> </div> </div> </div> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
